A basic Flask application can be created using only a few lines of Python code.


flaskEg1.py:


from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "Welcome to Flask!"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)



When the application runs, open the following address in a browser:
http://127.0.0.1:5000














